POWER BI DATA ANALYSIS EXPRESSION (DAX)

1. UNION('TABLE_1','TABLE_2') --> only when the columns are same. It removes duplicate values

2. UNIONALL('TABLE_1','TABLE_2') --> only when the columns are same. It keeps duplicate value

3. SUM('COL_1', 'COL_2') --> addition 

4. COUNT('COL_1') -> counts the number of values in a column

5. COUNTROWS('TABLE_NAME')--> counts number of rows in a table

6. DISTINCTCOUNT('COL_1') --> distinct values in the column

7. SUMX('TABLE','EXPRESSION')--> creates for all rows based on expression given

8. WEEKDAY('DATE_COL',1/2/3) --> It will give us the day of the week

9. IF('LOGICAL_TEST', 'RESULT_IF_TRUE', 'RESULT_IF_FALSE') --> If conditions are met it is true else it is false

10. FIND('FIND_TEXT', 'WITHINTEXT','START_POSITION', 'NOT_FOUND_VALUE') --> It finds the text in the column and returns values which is stated. 
    Start position is the one from where it starts.
   
11. CALCULATE('EXPRESSION', 'FILTERS') --> evaluates a expression in context modified by filters
 -- You can use IN clause also in calculate. Put your conditions inside { } --> Curly bracket 
 
12. SWITCH('EXPRESSION', 'VALUE1', 'RESULT1', ...'[ELSE]') --> Returns different results based on expression
13. CALENDAR('START_YEAR', 'END_YEAR') --> Calendar is used to define start year and end year

14. CALENDARAUTO() --> It creates dates in one column calculated from model automatically

15. DATE('YEAR', 'MONTH', 'Date') --> Date goes in year, month and date format

16. FORMAT('VALUE','format' ) --> converts value to text in the specified number format

17. ADDCOLUMNS('col1', 'col2'....'coln')---> adding column in table

18. VAR --> is declared before every variable

19. RETURN ---> Adds the following values in the table

20. WEEKNUM('Date', 'Return Type')--> returns week number in table

21. QUARTER('Date') --> Returns number from 1(Jan-Mar) to 4(Oct-Dec) representing the quarter

22. YEAR('Date')--> Returns year as four digit integer

23. NOW()--> Returns the current date and time in datetime format

24. DATEDIFF('DATE1', 'DATE2', 'INTERVAL') --> Returns number of units(days, years) between two input dates

25. EDATE('START DATE', MONTH) --> It gives before(use negative) or after(use positive) the date specified

26. EOMONTH('START DATE', MONTH)--> It gives before(use negative) or after(use positive) the date specified
